# DWGExport Help files

## How to use this macro
This macrco will enable the user to automatically export DWG for the selected views/sheets in a revit model

1. **Destination Directory:**

    Paste the location of the folder where you would like to have the DWGs saved 

2. **Export options:**  
    * All Views in Model

             Exports all views in the model

    * All Sheets in Model
        
            Exports all sheets in the model

    * View Name Contains
        
             Exports multiple views whose view name contains the text entered in the "Text To Search" field
    
    * View Name Equals
        
             Exports views matching the given view name
    
    * Sheet Name Contains
        
             Exports multiple sheets whose sheet name contains the text entered in the "Text To Search" field

    * Sheet Name Equals
        
             Exports sheets matching the given sheet name
         
    * View Set
        
            Exports all sheets and views in the View set whose name is provided in the "Text To Search" field

3. **Text To Search/View Set Name:**
    
    Enter the value to be searched in "View Name" / "Sheet Name" / "View Set Name"

4. **Dwg File Name:**

    * View Name Only

            View name will be assigned to Dwg file name (ViewName.dwg)

    * Project Name Only
        
            Project name will be assigned to Dwg file name (ProjectName.dwg)

    * Project Name and View Name 
        
            Project name and View name will be assigned to Dwg file name (ProjectName_Viewname.dwg)

5. **DWG Export Options:**

    Please modify the rest of the parameters based on your needs



